\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 The sonification is broken down by chemical emission, with each sonification representing an element observed: silicon, sulfur, calcium, iron, and the remaining high energy primarily from the blast wave. We represented each layer as a unique note on string instruments, with the volume indicating the locations brightness. The notes order reflected the relative frequencies of light shown in each layer (higher notes corresponded to higher frequencies).\'a0
