\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 The final sonification is the deepest x-ray image ever taken, revealing light emitted by extremely distant supermassive black holes created within a few billion years of the Big Bang. The data revealed hundreds of points of light, with their color indicating the energy of the X-ray energy detected. The image maps pixel color to musical notes. Red through violet were represented as low to high tones, mirroring the trend in their X-ray frequencies. We reduced the image resolution by a factor of four to allow more audible, consistent tones. 
